ENTRY            A0443   20260130   20260327   20260327       A130
SUBENT        A0443001   20260130   20260327   20260327       A130
BIB                 12         29
TITLE      Determination of the 9Be(alpha,n)12C reaction rate
AUTHOR     (R.Kunz,S.Barth,A.Denker,H.W.Drotleff,J.W.Hammer,
           H.Knee,A.Mayer)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,53,2486,1996)
INSTITUTE  (2GERTHS)
FACILITY   (DYNAM,2GERTHS)
SAMPLE     The beryllium targets were solid metallic targets
           evaporated on a copper backing. The exact determination
           of the target thickness has been done using the narrow
            resonance at alpha-particle energy=620 keV.
DETECTOR   (HE3SP) The detector consists of a cylindrical
           polyethylene moderator and a matrix of 16 3He-filled
           proportional counters.
METHOD     (SITA,BCINT)
           (EXTB) The beam energy has been calibrated using
           graphite targets and a narrow resonance at 1056.3-keV
           of the reaction 13C(alpha,n)16O.
STATUS     (TABLE,,R.Kunz+,J,PR/C,53,2486,1996) Tables were
           received from R.Kunz. (Data presented on figures in
           the article.)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty.
ADD-RES    (RRATE) Analytical expression of the reaction rate is
           given.
           Astrophysical factor.
HISTORY    (20020908C)
           (20020906R) The data tables were received from R.Kunz.
           (20020913U) Last checking has been done.
           (20260130A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           ERR-T -> DATA-ERR. Subents 006 and 007 were merged.
ENDBIB              29
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           32
SUBENT        A0443002   20260130   20260327   20260327       A130
BIB                  4          9
REACTION   (4-BE-9(A,N)6-C-12,,MLT,,REL)
           Yield curve. No any other information about units.
COMMENT    - By authors: Because the 9Be(alpha,n)12C yield is
           several orders of magnitude larger than the yield from
           the backing, neutrons arising from background reactions
           could be neglected.
STATUS     (COREL,A0443003) Data from 7.83E-07 at/b thick sample
HISTORY    (20260130A) SD: SF6=PY -> MLT in REACTION code.
           BIB updated. ERR-T -> DATA-ERR.
ENDBIB               9
COMMON               1          3
THICKNESS
ATOMS/B
   5.18E-07
ENDCOMMON            3
